<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[192,1440,1310,1558]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1898" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1898" box="[232,587,1310,1334]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anna">
<emphasis box="[232,419,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Pamphila anna</emphasis>
Mabille, 1898
</taxonomicName>
was previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[888,1120,1310,1334]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[888,968,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Vidius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[973,1120,1310,1334]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1134,1187,1310,1334]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Narga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vidius">
<emphasis box="[1282,1440,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Narga vidius</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
), but is not monophyletic with it (
<figureCitation box="[770,901,1342,1366]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Fig. 11â€“12</figureCitation>
). Instead, it groups closely with 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Moeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1375,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Moeris</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[356,410,1374,1398]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Geyer, [1832]" authorityName="Geyer" authorityYear="1832" box="[513,860,1374,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Talides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striga">
<emphasis box="[513,683,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Talides striga</emphasis>
Geyer, [1832]
</taxonomicName>
): compare with its sister, the 
<taxonomicName authority="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2019" authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[1229,1334,1374,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Viridina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1229,1334,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Viridina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1350,1434,1375,1399]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, cluster in 
<figureCitation box="[316,401,1406,1430]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[464,497,1406,1430]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">12</figureCitation>
. Despite obvious differences in wing patterns, the wing shapes and genitalia structures (even the shape of the valva with a somewhat expanded harpe) are quite similar between these species. The COI barcode difference between 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1898" box="[829,926,1471,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anna">
<emphasis box="[829,926,1471,1494]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">P. anna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Geyer" authorityYear="1832" box="[990,1103,1471,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Talides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striga">
<emphasis box="[990,1103,1471,1494]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">M. striga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 7.4%, suggesting a close relationship. For these reasons, instead of proposing a new genus name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1807" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1898" box="[1104,1198,1503,1526]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anna">
<emphasis box="[1104,1198,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">P. anna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we establish a new combination, 
<emphasis box="[357,518,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[357,510,1535,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Moeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anna">Moeris anna</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
